header.gameNote: NORTHEAST CONF TR AT SACRED HEART

article.headline: Sacred Heart 100, Wagner 68
article.story: FAIRFIELD, Conn. (AP) -- Joey Henley scored 20 points and grabbed 11 rebounds as Sacred Heart routed Wagner 100-68 in a quarterfinal game of the Northeast Conference tournament. The second-seeded Pioneers (17-13), in their eighth season in the NEC, recorded their first league tournament win. They advance to play No. 3-seeded Quinnipiac on Sunday. Quinnipiac beat Fairleigh Dickinson 78-77 in their quarterfinal Thursday. Jarrid Frye and Brice Brooks each scored 16 points for Sacred Heart. Drew Shubik added 14 points and Ryan Litke. 12. Matt Vitale led seventh-seeded Wagner (11-19) with 20 points. James Ulrich had 12. The Pioneers never trailed, opening a 15-4 lead en route to a 44-25 advantage at halftime. They led by as many as 37 in the second half. The victory also marked the first postseason Division I win for longtime coach Dave Bike. In his 29th season at Sacred Heart, Bike guided the Pioneers to the NCAA Division II national championship in 1985-86. Sacred Heart moved from Division II to Division I in 1999.
